2 (l) The provisions of this section prohibiting discrimination on the basis of
3 criminal history shall not be construed to prohibit or prevent an employer from
4 discharging or refusing to hire an individual for a position:
5 (1) for which any federal or State law or regulation creates a mandatory
6 or presumptive disqualification based on one or more types of criminal
7 offenses for which the individual has been convicted or is subject to a pending
8 criminal charge;
9 (2) if the employer or an affiliate of the employer is subject to an
10 obligation imposed by any federal or State law or regulation not to employ in
11 that position any individual who has been convicted of one or more types of
12 criminal offenses for which the individual has been convicted or is subject to a
13 pending criminal charge; or
14 (3) that bears a substantial relationship to one or more types of criminal
15 offenses for which the individual has been convicted or is subject to a pending
16 criminal charge.
